      ],
      "subtasks": [],
      "created": "2017-11-29T23:24:41.790+0000",
      "description": "When reacquiring containers after a nodemanager restart the Linux container executor invokes the container executor to essentially kill -0 the process to check if it is alive.  It would be a lot cheaper on Linux to stat the /proc/<pid> directory which the nodemanager can do directly rather than pay for the fork-and-exec through the container executor and potential signal permission issues.\r\n",
